race.comment: NATOYA (2) has settled well back in her two races this prep then worked through the line powerfully to pick up minor prizes. Lightly raced mare who gets this deep into a prep for the first time so might be ready to go to a new level. SURREAL I AM (1) went poorly over 1500m here last time out following a tough win in a similar contest the start prior. Is now nine runs into the campaign - big chance but need to trust he hasn't trained off. THINK WE'RE THERE (3) last appeared a month ago when easily accounted for by SURREAL I AM over 1500m here. Subsequent trial winner who can improve at the third run back. THEBES (8) can do better dropping back a little in grade and drawing an ideal gate. UNCLE HARRY (6) is best of the others following a tidy win at Port Macquarie last start.
